<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Khorkina Wins Women's All-Around Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Svetlana Khorkina of Russia
claimed the title of the women's all-around event at the World
Gymnastics Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Khorkina, who won the silver medal in the all-around at the
world championships in Sabae, Japan, in 1995, scored 38.636
points. She finished ahead of Romanian Simona Amanar, who had
38.587 points, and fellow Russian Elena Produnova, who was third
with 38.549 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
