<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cardiology Symposium In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Second Symposium on
Interventional Cardiology opened in the Great Hall of People in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Cardiologists, scholars, and doctors from 13 countries and
regions attended the symposium, which is sponsored by the Fuwai
Heart Hospital of the Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences and
Japan's Shonan Kamakura General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was an occasion to mark the twentieth anniversary
of the first percutaneous transluminal coronary angioplasty (PTCA)
operation, a major method in interventional cardiology used on a
heart patient in Europe.
</P>
<P>
PTCA is a standard method used on patients with coronary heart
disease, which involves inserting an instrument or medicine into
the blood vessel of diseased parts. It causes less pain and speeds
up recovery time.
</P>
<P>
The first operation of this sort was performed in China in 1984.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day symposium, experts will lecture on invasive
therapy in coronary heart disease, valvular heart disease and
arrhythmias, said Yin Dakui, the Chinese Vice-Minister of Health.
</P>
<P>
Participants will also discuss new topics in the treatment of
heart diseases and watch the live demonstration on invasive
procedures for coronary heart disease.
</P>
<P>
"I believe this symposium will promote interventional
cardiology in China," Yin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
