<HEADLINE> Floods Bring Death Toll to 342 in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Recent gushing floods and
tormenting rains in Pakistan have devoured 342 lives besides
extensively damaging the standing crops, emergency relief
officials said today.
</P>
<P>
The Federal government has asked the administration of all the
four provinces to submit details of the damages to ascertain the
actual losses, they said.
</P>
<P>
These details, the officials said, will be presented before
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif for the approval of compensation for
the victims from the PM's Relief Fund.  
</P>
</TEXT>
