<HEADLINE> Cyprus Condemns Jerusalem Bomb Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot government today
condemned Thursday's fatal bomb attack in Jerusalem and urged a
revival of the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"We unreservedly condemn the acts of violence which occurred
in Jerusalem. Violence must be repelled and cast aside so that
reason and dialog can take its place," Government Spokesman
Manolis Christofides said at his daily press briefing.
</P>
<P>
"Violence does not solve problems. The peaceful process must
be maintained for differences to be resolved," he added.
</P>
<P>
Seven people were killed and nearly 200 others injured in a
triple bombing in the heart of Jerusalem. The Islamic militant
group Hamas has claimed responsibility for the blast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
