<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientist Reaction To President's Comments On Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Scientists in Beijing agree
said today that President Jiang Zemin's remarks on scientific and
technological development has greatly encouraged the 600,000
scientists and technicians in China's colleges and universities.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from several Beijing universities and colleges
agreed that the remarks, which emphasize the importance of basic
research, should serve as a guiding principle in developing
China's science and technology for a long time.
</P>
<P>
Jin Guofan, an academic with the Chinese Academy of
Engineering, said that, since the beginning of the reforms and
opening-up, basic research conditions have improved a great deal,
contributing a lot to progress.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yue, president of Beijing Polytechnic University, pointed
out that the increasing reforms of the science and technology
structure of universities depends on a perfect combination of
teaching, research, and training of personnel.
</P>
<P>
Wei Yu, vice minister in charge of the State Education
Commission, described the institutes of higher learning as a major
source of China's professionals, and called this a glorious
historical mission for all science and technology personnel in
helping the country take its proper place in global science and
technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
