<HEADLINE> German, Italian Companies Plan Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- German engineering group
Mannesmann has announced its plan for a telecommunication joint
venture with Italy's Olivetti, in which it would take a 49.9
percent stake, according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The scheme, with a view to strengthening Olivetti's position in
Italy's telecommucation market, will involve Olivetti's Omnitel
and Infostrada units.
</P>
<P>
Olivetti's Omnitel is the second largest mobile phone operator
in Italy while its Infostrada is the largest private competitor to
Telecom Italia.
</P>
<P>
According to a Mannesmann statement, it would also take a 25
percent share in a capital injection and convertible loan for
Olivetti. 
</P>
