<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trade Fair In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 5 (Xinhua) -- A provincial-level trade fair
has helped China's land-locked province of Hunan open its door to
the outside world much wider.
</P>
<P>
Hunan signed a record of 242 project contracts at the Sixth
Hunan Trade Fair that closed in the capital city of Changsha
today, involving nearly three billion US dollars of investment.
</P>
<P>
About half of the foreign investment has been used for
infrastructure projects like road, bridges, and power stations.
</P>
<P>
Many agricultural and technical renovation projects at large
and medium-sized state-run enterprises also got financial support
from foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair also helped Hunan's foreign trade sector open
new markets in a dozen of African, Latin American, and South
Pacific countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
