<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Paraguay Stadium Roof Caves in Killing 35 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-five people have
been confirmed killed and another 190 injured after a tornado
caused a sports stadium roof to collapse on a crowd in Ciudad Del
Este, Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here on Friday, some of those
killed were decapitated by the falling metal structure and
several of the injured were in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Several children were trampled under foot by hundreds of people
who fled the stadium in panic after the accident shortly after
midnight.
</P>
<P>
The stadium roof, retaining cement columns, and a 50-meter
stretch of wall underneath the bleachers collapsed when the
building was hit by a tornato during a violent thunderstorm,
reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
