<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor On Commercial Centers In Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 5 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Li Tieying,
speaking today in the capital of central China's Henan province,
said that reforming the economic system is the key to establishing
commercial trade centers in central and western China.
</P>
<P>
Li told a national conference on establishing commercial trade
centers in these areas that the central authorities have always
attached great importance to development there. "The pilot project
to establish several commercial and trade centers in the region
will bring common development of primary, secondary, and tertiary
industries, as well as that of surrounding urban and rural
economies."
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the three cities of Lanzhou, Zhengzhou, and Chengdu
became pilot cities in the project, and Li urged people of the
region to learn from the 15th National Congress and help the
reform of the economic system, to promote economic expansion in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the central and western regions should
conscientiously study General Secretary Jiang Zemin's speech at
the Party School on May 29, hold high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, and combine public ownership with a market
economy to accelerate economic development in the region," Li
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
