<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 400 S. African Policemen Died in Murders, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Since the beginning of
this year, 321 police officers were murdered and 85 committed
suicide in South Africa, national police commmissioner George
Fivaz said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a tree planting ceremongy in Pretoria to
commemorate Arbor day and to remember fallen colleagues, Fivaz
said a way had to be found to protect the police.
</P>
<P>
"If we don't stand together to fight these senseless attacks
on police officers, we are going to have a real threat against
our democracy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said car accidents this year had claimed the lives of 133
police officers throughout the country, noting "we are suffering
huge losses in our police service every year, and we have to find
a way to protect our protectors."
</P>
<P>
According to a police spokesman, 210 officers were murdered
last year, and 160 committed suicide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
