<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador Offers Condolences to Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PENOM PENH, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador to
Cambodia Yan Tingai today offered his condolences to the 29
Chinese compatriots killed in a plane crash at Cambodia's
Pochentong airport Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yan presented wreath to the victims of whom 19 from Taiwan,
four from Hong Kong, two from inland China and one from Macao,
at the mourning hall in the Calmette hospital of Penom Penh.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador also expressed sympathy and solicitude to the
relatives of the victims, who expressed sincere gratitude for the
help provided by the Chinese embassy.
</P>
<P>
Another 36 people aboard the Vietnam Airlines Tupolev-134 plane
were killed in the crash assumed to be a result of bad weather
while only one Thai boy survived.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia flied flags at half-mast today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
