<HEADLINE> COSCO Global Communications Network In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The COSCO Global
Communications Network in China's largest commercial center got a
thorough going over today to improve communications facilities for
China's oceangoing ships significantly.
</P>
<P>
The network was built by China Ocean Shipping Companies (COSCO)
Group, the leading ocean shipper in China, with 11 major nodal
points in China and overseas.
</P>
<P>
Inter-group communications in COSCO and with clients previously
went through the public telecommunications network, and the cost
for land telecommunications alone amounted to more than 200
million yuan each year.
</P>
<P>
With the special network, COSCO can run communications with its
agents in more than 1,100 ports in many countries through the
network, paying only for lease of telecommunications lines.
</P>
<P>
While special telecommunications networks have been built by
most consortia globally, only a few China's businesses have been
able to do so.  
</P>
