<HEADLINE> Asian Professional Basketball League to be Formed Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Basketball
Confederation (ABC) announced here on Friday that it will kick off
its first professional league next year.
</P>
<P>
At the organization's Central Board meeting and Congress held
here today, ABC decided to form the inaugural professional league
by the time between August to October next year.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the eight-team League will be teams from
China, Japan, South Korea, Chinese Taipei, the Philippines,
Malaysia, Indonesia and Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
The league matches will take a formula similar to that taken by
the U.S. National Basketball Association (NBA), according to ABC
President Carl Ching Man Ky. The Asian governing body for the
game has contacted NBA for technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
In order to raise the local standard of play, the Hong Kong
Basketball Association is considering proposals of inviting
players from China's mainland to join in the local club teams. The
association is also considering to invite former NBA players to
play in Hong Kong. 
</P>
