<HEADLINE> Funeral of Diana's Chauffeur Indefinitely Put off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The funeral of Henri Paul, the
chauffeur of Princess Diana and her friend Dodi Al Fayed, was put
off today because his family wanted to counter check how much
alcohol was in his bloodstream when he crashed the Mercedes early
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Paul's funeral was originally scheduled for Saturday in Lorient
on the western coast of France, which is his hometown. No new date
was set for the funeral, according to Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
A counter-examination by experts were going on today to
reevaluate the level of alcohol in Paul's bloodstream at the
demand of his family, said AFP.
</P>
<P>
A primary examination by investigators showed that there was
1.75-1.85 grams of alcohol in each liter of his blood, a rate much
higher than the 0.5 gram limit allowed by the law for driving.
</P>
<P>
Paul was employed by the Hotel Ritz of Paris in 1986 as a
security man. He lost control of the Mercedes which carried Diana
and Dodi and their bodyguard early Sunday morning when the car
crashed at the Alma tunnel in downtown Paris, killing Diana and
Dodi. 
</P>
