<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Credit for Senegal Health Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of a credit of 50 million U.S. dollars
equivalent to support Senegal's integrated health sector
development program.
</P>
<P>
The program will help improve the health status of the
Senegalese population and accelerate the Western African country's
transition toward slower population growth.
</P>
<P>
The program will achieve the goal through the support of
policies and investments designed to improve the quality, access,
and sustainability of health delivery systems.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending wing for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
