<HEADLINE> UK Queen Back in London, Meets Diana Mourners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Queen and other
members of the royal family returned to London from Scotland today
and have met thousands of Diana mourners outside royal palaces.
</P>
<P>
The Queen, dressed all in black, and her husband Prince Philip
inspected a carpet of flowers outside Buckingham Palace Friday
afternoon, meeting and speaking to mourners there, acknowledging
their grief and sympathy.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Queen and her husband paid their respects at
the coffin of Princess Diana in St James's Palace.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prince Charles and Diana's two sons Princes William,
15, and Harry, 12, also inspected the thousands of tributes to
Diana outside Kensington Palace, Diana's home in London.
</P>
<P>
The princes took bouquets from the crowd and placed them among
those already lying against the gates of the palace.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time the Queen and princes had appeared
among the mourners ever since Diana's tragic death in a car crash
in Paris last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Queen is expected to make a live broadcast to the nation
from Buckingham Palace at 17:00 GMT.
</P>
<P>
The funeral of Diana will take place on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
