<HEADLINE> South Korea Beats Kazakhstan in World Cup qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 6 (Xinhua) -- South Korea beat Kazakhstan 3-0
with a Choi Yong-Soo hat-trick in a World Cup Asia Zone qualifying
match here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Favored South Korea overwhelmed their opponent in this opening
match of the Asia qualifying group B competitions.
</P>
<P>
South Korea, seeking a fourth consecutive berth in the World
Cup finals, attacked throughout the match at the Olympic Stadium
in southern Seoul which ended with just 10 Kazakhstan players on
the field.
</P>
<P>
Choi opened the scoring when he latched on to a cross from Seo
Jung-Won in the 24th minute an forced in a strong header.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old striker scored his second goal with a low shot
in the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
Choi completed his hat-trick, and sealed the game in the 74th
minute with another header, this time from a free kick from Ha
Suk-Joo. 
</P>
