<HEADLINE> First Racing Season of HKSAR Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A grand ceremony was held
here today to mark the opening of the first horse racing season of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
After a two-month summer break, more than 40,000 racing fans
gathered again at the Happy Valley Racecourse, Wanchai of Hong
Kong Island, to enjoy an exciting weekend.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the HKSAR, was invited to
open the season by beating a huge gong. Today's inaugural running
was called the HKSAR Chief Executive's Cup.
</P>
<P>
A Shanxi drum band and an Inner Mongolian dancing troupe were
invited to add to the enthusiasm, while a number of famous local
theatrical stars also performed at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The racing season will last until June of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The organizer of the racing, the Hong Kong Jockey Club, is a
non-profit making organization. Over the past years it has
donated billions of Hong Kong dollars to various charitable and
community projects through its charities trust. 
</P>
</TEXT>
