<HEADLINE> AIPO Issues a 72-Point Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The 18th meeting of the ASEAN
Inter-Parliament Organization (AIPO) Working Committee ended last
night in Indonesia's resort island of Bali, with the issuance of a
72-point resolution on the political, economic and social sectors.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which was closed by its president , Speaker of
Indonesia's House of Representatives Wahono, appointed Speaker of
Malaysia's Parliament Tan Sri Datuk Muhammad Zhai Ismail as next
president, reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting which was opened by Indonesian President Suharto
last Monday, has decided that the 19th meeting of the AIPO Working
Committee will be held in Malaysia in August next year.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the meeting, Theo l. Sambuaga, said the five-day
meeting ran smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the AIPO's Political Committee Tati
Dharsoyo said the AIPO has also discussed the Cambodian issue.
</P>
<P>
"But it does not mean that the AIPO is interfering in
Cambodia's internal conflict. We just want the conflict to end
immediately in the peaceful way," he said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also issued a joint communique, calling for closer
cooperation among the ASEAN countries in political, economic and
social fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
