<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK-Beijing Powered Paragliding Rally to Start Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- After three-year efforts and
two postpones, a historic powered paragliding rally from Hong Kong
to Beijing is at last to be kicked off here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Due to short of funding, organizers of the 17-day Hong
Kong-Beijing Powered Paragliding Rally '97 had to cut the
participating field by half to only eight machines.
</P>
<P>
The powered paraglides are to be flown by eight pilots, five
from China's mainland and three from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The pilots are to take off Sunday morning, fly nine kilometers
across the border between Hong Kong and south China's Guangdong
Province into Shenzhen. They are to land at an amusement park in
the western suburbs.
</P>
<P>
From there, they would continue to travel on the rally by land
and air through the Chinese provinces of Guangdong, Hunan, Hubei,
Henan and Hebei before reaching the destination of capital city
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
There are 16 special timing stages on the Rally's 3,000
kilometers route, with participating pilots competing each other
in speed, endurance and circular races. The Rally ends on
September 23 at the Great Wall, north of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The final placings are to be decided according to their
respective accumulated points from the races.
</P>
<P>
The Rally is jointly organized by the Aero Sports Federation of
China and the Hong Kong Paragliding Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
