<HEADLINE> Chinese Exhibition On Half Decade Of Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of China's
achievements in economic construction and ethical and cultural
progress since the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) in 1992 opened at the Beijing Exhibition Center
today.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a Standing Committe member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee, speaking at the opening ceremony,
said that the Chinese people will win "new victories" in the
socialist cause by adhering to Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said, "In the past five years, the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core has led the whole Party and
the people of the whole country ... in making tremendous
achievements in deepening reforms, opening wider to the outside
world, promoting development and maintaining stability."
</P>
<P>
Hu attributed the achievements to the following of Deng's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Zou Jiahua opened the exhibition. The ceremony was
attended by Ding Guangen, Li Lanqing, Li Tieying, Wu Bangguo,
Jiang Chunyun, Wei Jianxing, and other leaders, and some 3,000
people.
</P>
<P>
