<HEADLINE> Economists Assess Private Economy's Role in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Economists attending a seminar
on China's private economic development in Beijing on Friday said
that the sector role in the country's economic take-off has been
growing, according to China Securities today.
</P>
<P>
China's private economy is an important, organic part of the
socialist economy, and is playing a major role in the economy.
</P>
<P>
They said that a pressing matter for future development of the
private sector is reinforcing management and planning to ensure
healthy development.
</P>
<P>
They called for an environment that allows the private economy
to compete equally with other economies, one that is part of the
law to protect private properties, while protecting public
property.
</P>
<P>
Private entrepreneurs should improve themselves and the
management of private firms as well.
</P>
<P>
From 1978 to 1996, the country's national economy grew at eight
percent annually, but the private sector grew 25 percent annually
and it has contributed 80 percent of the increase of the national
economy as a whole in recent years, according to the
economists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
