<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 200 Rebels Captured and Deserted in N. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 rebels of the Lord's
Resistance Army (LRA) have been captured or deserted from their
leader, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Colonel James Kazini, the commander of the fourth division,
said that yesterday when he informed the situation in the north
to lt. colonel Kale Kayihura, the army chief political commissar
and in a press conference yesterday in northern city of Gulu.
</P>
<P>
Another 18 rebel soldiers have been killed earlier yesterday
in the northern district of Kitgum, other officers in the
division added.
</P>
<P>
The death rate is high in the ranks of LRA, Kazini added.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Kazini appealed the abducted civilians in the LRA
ranks to report to the authorities.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Kony penetrated into Uganda from southern Sudan on
August 24 with 300 of his men to show his presence, an earlier
report said.
</P>
<P>
LRA is a rebel group acting in the north which launched a
11-year war against the present regime of president Yoweri
Museveni. LRA had thousands of members in the past, but an
earlier official report put the number of the rebels at around
450. LRA has bases in southern Sudan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
