<HEADLINE> Health Official Urges Malaysians to improve Personal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The personal hygiene
level of Malaysians is still low and several diseases are related
to the poor personal hygiene, a senior health official said today.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysians are found neglecting personal hygiene and
cleanliness of their surroundings and diseases like dengue fever,
food poisonings, Hepatitis A prevailing are related to personal
hygiene, Health Director- General Abu Bakar Suleiman said.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that the future generation pay more attention to
personal hygiene, more health programs would be introduced in
schools, the director-general told reporters after opening the
Malaysian Pediatricians Association Annual Congress in Kota
Baharu, capital of the northeastern state of Kelantan, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
Parents also have important role to play in setting a good
example for their children, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the shortage of specialists for Intensive Care
Units in hospitals, which was caused by the lack of interest among
pediatricians was being looked into.
</P>
<P>
A total of 350 pediatricians including those from abroad are
attending the three-day congress with the theme "Malaysian Health
Vision 2020, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
