<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Kills 11 in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Eleven people were killed and
21 others injured in a road accident Friday afternoon in the
Republic of Dagestan, of Russia, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Most of the killed and injured were on a bus crashed head-on by
an oil tanker swerving out of its lane, the Russian National
Emergency Board was quoted as saying this morning.
</P>
<P>
It took place on the highway linking Dagestan's capital of
Makhachkala to the southern part of the republic, said the
authorities, which have launched a probe into its cause. 
