<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Returns to HK from Maiden Overseas Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa returned to Hong
Kong today after concluding his visit to Malaysia and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of Tung's first overseas trip since he took
office was to get across the message that it was "business as
usual" in Hong Kong after the handover.
</P>
<P>
"I was there to explain ... that we are going forward well,
that the government is functioning normally, lifestyle we are
accustomed to is maintained and economy continuing to expand,"
Tung told a press conference upon his arrival at the Kai Tak
Airport.
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad to say that the message that we were trying to get
across that Hong Kong is doing well, is well received," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Tung pointed out the cordial and warm welcome he and his
entourage received demonstrated how much importance the two
Southeast Asian neighbors attached to their relationship with Hong
Kong and with China.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Tung met with Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad and Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views about many issues of mutual interest to
see "whether we can deepen our cooperation", in particular, in the
areas of housing, education and information technology, Tung said,
describing the tour as "constructive and useful."
</P>
<P>
After a short break, Tung will be flying to the United States
on Monday and is expected to meet U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
</TEXT>
