<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Help Southern Africa Clear Landmines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BLANTYPE (Malawi), September 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Union
has pledged to donate 2.07 million ECU to the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) to aid the region in its
anti-personnel landmine clearance campaign.
</P>
<P>
This is an additional sum to the two million ECU granted to
SADC out of a total of 3.5 million ECU made available by the EU
to the UN for landmine clearance in various parts of the world,
Alfred Nzo, chairman of the sub-regional organization said here
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nzo, who is also foreign minister of South Africa, said at a
press conference after the conclusion of the SADC ministerial
council meeting in the eve of the Monday SADC summit, said that
the group is aimed at a total ban on anti-personnel landmines in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The southern Africa is one of the areas in the world where
landmines have posed as a dangerous threat to innocent people's
life, Nzo said.
</P>
<P>
In Angola, one of the SADC members, alone, there are an
estimated 20 million landmines littered throughout the country,
exceeding the number of the country's population.
</P>
<P>
The death of Princess Diana in a car crash in Paris, with the
funeral to be held today, has added a high-profile impetus to the
landmine clearance campaign in the region, several attendants for
the ministers' conference said.
</P>
<P>
In March this year, Diana came to Angola as part of the
British Red Cross Campaign for Landmine Clearance.
</P>
<P>
According to Nzo, apart from the continued cooperation with
EU, SADC will also seek to tighten its ties with other regional
and international organizations, such as the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), the African Development Bank (ADB), and the
Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA).
</P>
<P>
An agreement on SADC-ADB cooperation is to be submitted to the
1997 SADC summit to be held on Monday, the SADC official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
