<HEADLINE> East African Passport to Be Issued in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The first batch of the East
African passports will be out in the first week of November in
Kenya, Tanzania and Uganda, the three member states of the East
African Cooperation (EAC), local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Currently as many as 100,000 copies of the common travel
document are being printed for each member state, EAC Executive
Secretary Francis Muthaura said at the second meeting of the
attorney-generals of EAC members.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting to end in Kenya's Indian Ocean port
Mombasa today, is expected to adopt and sign the draft on a
common road transport policy treaty.
</P>
<P>
Participants also dwelt on EAC policy-making and common legal
and judicial operation so as to strengthen cooperation among the
three countries.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda and Burundi sent observers to the meeting. 
</P>
