into Lebanon Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio reported today that the prime minister did not
rule out the possibility to release Iranian-backed Hezbollah
prisoners in exchange for the soldier's body, which was
reportedly taken away by Hezbollah from the scene of the fighting,
</P>
<P>
Some 11 Israeli navy commandos were killed and another was
missing Thursday night during a clash with Hezbollah gunmen north
of the Tyre in south Lebanon. The missing in the action is
believed to be dead, an Israeli army spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai
demanded the Lebanese Army and International Red Cross seek
the return of the commando's body. He also noted that military
inquiry is examing all stages of the operation with the
intelligence help.
</P>
<P>
The United States has promised to help in the search for the
missing commando, and it called on all sides in south Lebanon to
show restraint.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. State Department official told Israel Radio that his
country has never opposed Israeli actions against terrorists
north of the "security zone", but "it must be remembered that
Israel is operating on Lebanese sovereign territory."
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 15-mile-wide "security zone" in South Lebanon
in 1985 to prevent cross-border attacks by anti-Israeli
Hezbollah guerrillas who have been fighting to force Israel out
of the Lebanese territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
