<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Start Power Rationing on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Power rationing is to
start next Monday throughout Tanzania, according to a statement
from the Tanzania Electric Supply Company (TANESO) available here
last night.
</P>
<P>
The statement said residential areas in Dar es Salaam and
Coastal regions will be divided into load shedding zones, each of
which will miss supply thrice a week from 6:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m.,
while power supply to industrial areas will be interrupted twice
a week also between 6:00 a.m. and 9:00 p.m.
</P>
<P>
TANECO regional managers have been instructed to draw power
rationing schedules in their areas.
</P>
<P>
TANECO acting Managing Director Kiato Iranga said in the
statement that the load shedding is inevitable following acute
depletion of water at the generation reservoirs in Iringa.
</P>
<P>
As of September 5, the Mtera Dam water level was merely 1.15
meters above the minimum level while the Kidatu Dam water level
was only 11.90 meters above the minimum level.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania experienced power rationing four years ago which
necessitated the installation of the multi-billion shillings gas
turbines at Ubungo in Dar es Salaam which injected about 40
megawatts to the national power grid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
