<HEADLINE> Maradona Says He has Taken no Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Argentina soccer star
Diego Maradona denied Friday he has every taken drugs and said the
positive result of his doping test was tampered by his enemies in
the shadows.
</P>
<P>
"I'm dead inside. Until they tell me I can play again, I'm a
dead man," Maradona said on a television show.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that Maradona made his public appearance
since he tested positive for drugs after a recent league
match. The third doping scandal may end his sparkling soccer
career.
</P>
<P>
Maradona insisted he was the victim of a "sinister" force.
</P>
<P>
"I swear on my daughters that I took nothing, and when I do
that I'm telling the truth," he said on the show Fenomeno Real.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine Football Association (AFA) has summoned Maradona
to testify before its sanctions committee next Tuesday. A second
test this week confirmed he tested positive for drugs after the
August 24 match, in which he scored a penalty point for his club
Boca Juniors.
</P>
<P>
"If I had taken cocaine I wouldn't have gone to the match.
Cocaine doesn't help but rather hinders you on the pitch -- I know
I would see four balls and eight defenders," he argued.
</P>
<P>
In a last ditch attempt to ward off punishment, Maradona's
lawyers have demanded a DNA check to verify the urine tested was
his, but it was not clear when this would be carried out.
</P>
<P>
Guillermo Coppola, Maradona's manager who himself was arrested
on drugs charges last year, has said Maradona's drink may have
been spiked before the urine test. 
</P>
</TEXT>
