<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan Welcomes More Japanese Investment: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekistan hopes Japanese
businessmen to further invest in the country in order to widen
cooperation between the two nations, President Islam Karimov said
today in Uzbek capital Tashkent, Interfax agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Japanese Director-General of Economic
Plan Agency Taro Aso, Karimov said there are not yet enough Japanese
businesses in Uzbekistan.
</P>
