developing cooperation with the Central Asian countries, and
Japanese businessmen are ready for further action because they
consider Uzbekistan a good market.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also signed today documents on Japanese
government providing about 439 million yen (about 3.66
million U.S. dollars) to Uzbekistan in farming equipments and
museum facilities.
</P>
<P>
Japanese investment in Uzbekistan has amounted to one billion
U.S. dollars in four joint ventures and three ventures solely
owned by Japan. 
