<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Brazilian Internet Users Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazil has surpassed
Russia and some Asian countries and regions to rank 19th in
Internet users in just two years, a high-ranking official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting on software, Ivan Moura Campos from the
Science and Technology Ministry, said Brazil now has 1.1 million
people linked to the world wide web in 110 hosts.
</P>
<P>
From December of 1995 to July of 1997, the number of hosts in
Brazil grew by 536 percent, while that of commercial computers
connected to the Internet increased by 1,792 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, more than 1,000 suppliers of access to
Internet and up to 5,000 web information suppliers were
installed. 
</P>
