<HEADLINE> Gold Price Rises as Thai Currency Weakens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The weaker Thai currency
pushed gold price in Thailand further up to 5,600 baht (about 168
U.S. dollars) per baht weight (15 grams) Friday, from 5,505 baht
Monday, according to the Thai Farmers Research Center.
</P>
<P>
Friday the currency baht in onshore trading closed at 37.10 per
U.S. dollar, as compared with 38.40 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Over the last two months, gold is 31.76 percent (1,350 baht)
dearer than just before the baht was floated on July 2.
</P>
<P>
The Thai gold market, worth 30 billion baht (about 1 billion
U.S. dollars) a year, was also under pressure from the increase in
value-added tax from 7 percent to 10 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
