<HEADLINE> China Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper front-paged an article reviewing China's
gratifying achievements since the 14th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) five years ago, which have been
scored under the leadship of the Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core. This was the second in a new series of
articles to greet the forthcoming 15th CPC National Congress.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Japan should advance their bilateral friendship
for generations to come, said President Jiang Zemin during his
meeting with visiting Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto
Friday. Jiang also said the two countries should strictly observe
the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty of
Peace and Friendship when promoting bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
-- The third generation of the collective leadership of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) with Jiang Zemin at the core,
steadfastly carring out the independent foreign policy of peace
devised by their predecessors, has opened up new prospects for
China's diplomacy in the 1990s, especially since the 14th CPC
National Congress five years ago, said a commentary jointly
released by the Xinhua News Agency and the People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper carried in full text a circular issued by the
State Planning Commission on tightening the rein on charging of
illicit fees, fines and other fees against enterprises.
</P>
<P>
-- China has made noticeable achievements in the management of
the state assets in the past five years: the completion of a
nationwide examination has led to a clear evaluation of the state
assets; the registration of state assets has become standardized;
the assets appraising sector has been forging ahead, and so on.
</P>
<P>
-- Chairman of the Standing Committed of the National People's
Congress Qiao Shi, and Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji also held talks
with the visiting Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto
Friday. They stressed that the two countries should uphold the
principles and spirit of the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and
Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and Friendship, and use the
documents as the political basis for jointly advancing the steady
and healthy development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Early rice this year has another bumper harvest, climbing
4.5 percent over the next year to 45.78 million tons, according to
a survey by the Rural Social and Economic Investigation Team under
the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
-- A Senior Tibetan official said that rapid economic and
social development in Tibet is the result of constant assistance
from the Central government as well as other provinces and
regions, including human resources.
</P>
<P>
-- A recent report released by the the State Statistics Bureau
said that China continues to maintain a rapid economic growth,
which is expected to hit ten percent for 1997. 
</P>
