<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank Strengthens Fund Management of Finance Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China has
called for tighter controls over fund management by finance
companies of large enterprise groups in China.
</P>
<P>
It said they should keep outstanding loans to below 75 percent
of total deposits and that those with more loans than permitted
must draw up plans to cut loans until the number of outstanding
ones is below 75 percent of deposits, within a specified period of
time.
</P>
<P>
Finance companies should support large enterprise groups in
technical renovations and new product development, and should
concentrate on medium- and long-range banking services, it said,
adding that they should not be turned into a combination of
commercial bank and trust and investment company for the
enterprise group.
</P>
<P>
It said finance companies can not borrow more funds than their
registered capital, and can only borrow funds to meet temporary
fund shortages and can not use that for loans.
</P>
<P>
It also put limitations on their internal fund transfers, the
ratio of medium- and long-term funds, and how such funds should be
used. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
