<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibet Sets Goals to Balance County-Level Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Financial authorities of the
Tibet Autonomous Region have asked treasury officials at the
county level to balance their budget by the year 2,000.
</P>
<P>
The call was made at a regional financial conference held here
recently, with a view to advancing local economy into next century.
</P>
<P>
Local economic analysis indicates that Tibet is likely to have
a revenue income of 600 million yuan in the year 2,000, more than
double that of 1995.
</P>
<P>
By then, 11 counties would achieve a revenue exceeding 10
million yuan each while others are expected to see their treasury
grow at the rate of 15 percent each year in the next four years.
</P>
<P>
The present sound economic situation and the continual support
from the central government make it possible for Tibet to realize
its budget balance goal, which in turn would provide financial
support for the overall development of the region, according to
local economic experts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
