<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Province Develops Infrastructures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north
China has invested heavily in building infrastructures over the
past five years, aiming to lay a solid foundation for speedy and
sustainable economic development.
</P>
<P>
The investment grew at an annual rate of 40.3 percent,
according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
In the five years, over 371.2 billion yuan has been invested in
basic industries such as agriculture, energy and raw materials as
well as six infrastructural sectors of railway, highway, airport,
port, telecommunications and civil facilities.
</P>
<P>
Hebei's first civil airport, the Shijiazhuang Airport, was
built during the period.
</P>
<P>
The province now ranks third in the country in terms of the
length of expressways.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the province has constructed a number of big ports
for international shipping business.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
