<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 32 Illegal Ecuadoran Immigrants Held in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican Migration
authorities detained 32 Ecuadoran nationals who pretended to enter
Nicaragua en route to the United States, the authorities announced
today.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorans, 20 men and 12 women, who had IDs and passports,
traveled in the box of a cargo truck covered with a canvas,
accompanied by a driver and two traffickers, all Nicaraguans.
</P>
<P>
Each Ecuadoran had paid a sum of 300 U.S. dollars to the
traffickers to be taken to Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
The group entered Costa Rica through the Panamanian border.
</P>
<P>
Their migratory documents registered their entrance to Panama,
but not their exit or their entrance to Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
The Costa Rican migration authorities decided to send them back
to Panama, where the authorities of that country will decide if
they should be returned to their country of origin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
