<HEADLINE> Latin America Cultural News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are Latin
America cultural news briefs over the past few days:
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The renowned Mexican singer Luis Miguel will
perform in Argentina on November 14-15 to promote his new record
"Romance," it was reported here lately.
</P>
<P>
Luis Miguel presentation is part of a tour that will start
September 12 in the United States and continue through Central and
South America.
</P>
<P>
The previous visit of Luis Miguel to Argentina was in December
of last year, when he filled for two nights the River Plate
stadium in Buenos Aires.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian government will allocate 98 million
U.S. dollars to the education sector in the northeast to improve
the education conditions in that region, the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry stated that the states of Bahia, Ceara,
Maranhao, Paraiba, Piaui, Pernambuco, and Rio Grande de Norte will
receive from now until February of next year nearly 98 million
dollars to develop the Northeast Education Project.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Famous Venezuelan singer and composer Franco de
Vita will perform on October 3 in Santiago in a 2-hour concert,
accompanied by his 15 member permanent musicians ensemble, the
local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The artist's performance is part of his world tour of this year
called "Out of This World." The singer will sing his classic
themes such as "Te Amo" and "Calido y Frio." Franco de Vita will
accompany himself with his traditional grand piano.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Spanish singer Enrique Iglesias confirmed his
next South American tour and will perform on October 1 in Uruguay
in the Central Park of the Nacional Football Club of this city,
the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
The tour will include Argentina, Chile, Paraguay, Peru, Brazil,
and Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Enrique Iglesias, renowned singer Julio Iglesias' son, has
already sold 5 million records across the world. 
</P>
