<HEADLINE> US Aircraft Component Company Expanding in Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 6 (Xinhua) -- AlliedSignal Aerospace, one of
the world's leading suppliers of aircraft components, is making
inroads into the fast-growing Chinese market to capture a
significant share of the booming aerospace business.
</P>
<P>
The company will provide wheels and brakes for the five
Boeing-777 airplanes to be purchased by Air China, according to
Daniel Burnham, president of the company.
</P>
<P>
The effort will give a push to the increasing business of
AlliedSignal Aerospace in China, as Air China is the flag carrier
of China's civil aviation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The personnel training plan with China Aviation Industries
(CAI) will be furthered, he added.
</P>
<P>
Their cooperation began in 1996. So far, the US enterprise has
helped train 86 employees for the CAI. In addition, it will offer
scholarships for CAI staff this year.
</P>
<P>
AlliedSignal Aerospace's annual volume of business is as high
as 14 billion US dollars. It also provides repair and overhaul
service.  
</P>
