<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mao's Model Village Becomes County's Top Taxpayer (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Dazhai Village, which was
named a rural model by late Chinese Chairman Mao Zedong in the
1960s and 70s, has joined the market competition and become the
No. 1 taxpayer in Xiyang County, northern Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the village's properties were valued at 41 million
yuan, with an average per-capita income of 2,100 and pretax
profits of 1.64 million yuan. It paid the highest tax among all
the 423 villages in this moderately backward, agriculture-based
county.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the village has developed both agricultural and
industrial sectors, relying on its renowned "Dazhai Spirit" which
champions hard work.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991-1996 period, the village increased its
industrial output value from 2.6 million yuan to 36.2 million
yuan, while its grain output stood at 320,000 kg and the forest
coverage rate of the village's Hutou hill reaches more than 65
percent.
</P>
<P>
Villagers attributed the fast industrial development to the
setting-up of the Dazhai Economic Development Corporation in
1992. The company now owns a number of firms which produce wool
garments, shirts and cement, and a transport company.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture has named Dazhai's industrial and
trade park as "National Model Zone for East-West Cooperation Among
Township Enterprises."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mao's Model Village Becomes County's Top Taxpayer (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The speedy economic growth has improved the welfare of the
villagers. Currently, their per-capita residential space stands at
22 sq m, and their per-capita savings amounts to 1,056 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The villagers now enjoy free education for school-aged
children, pensions for the aged, free coal-supply, free
health-care, and cash prizes for those who enter universities and
secondary schools.
</P>
<P>
Dazhai residents no longer have to fetch water from far away,
manually transport fertilizer to farmland, or walk a long distance
to see doctor, since running water, village-owned vehicles and a
village clinic are now available.
</P>
<P>
However, the villagers are aiming higher, and are preparing for
a new round of development by establishing more industries with
funds from other parts of the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
