<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stadium Collapse Kills 32 in Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 5 (Xinhua) -- At least 32 people were
killed and 200 were injured when the roof and a wall of a football
stadium collapsed in Ciudad del Este early today, some 330
kilometers east of Asuncion, the Paraguayan capital.
</P>
<P>
Information received from Asuncion said that the metallic
structure of the stadium roof and a 70-meter long wall collapsed
because of a tornado and rainstorm that hit the zone when some
4,000 people were gathered in the February 3 Stadium for a
political rally to mark the close of the Colorado Party's campaign
to name a presidential candidate for the May 1998 elections.
</P>
<P>
The Telam Argentine state news agency reported that the
Paraguayan government decreed a three-day mourning in the Alto
Parana department, where Ciudad del Este locates, and the
suspension of the primary elections next Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Paraguayan President Juan Carlos Wasmosy ordered that four
transport planes and five ambulances be sent to the zone to assist
and transport the injured to hospitals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
