<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Changsha Launches Greening Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Changsha, capital of central
Chine's Hunan Province, recently launched a greening drive
designed to improve its ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to build within about four years a
green belt around the city, with a radius of 20 km.
</P>
<P>
The plan also calls for all city squares and various other
locations to be covered with vegetation.
</P>
<P>
A special team headed by Changsha Mayor Yuan Hankun will guide
the work of the greening project. The city has already provided
100 million yuan (12 million US dollars) in funding for the drive.
</P>
<P>
Changsha, one of the first 24 cities the State Council has
listed as famous ancient cities, is home to Mount Yuelu which sits
beside the Xiangjiang River in the city suburbs. Experts note that
Changsha has great potential for ecological development.
</P>
<P>
Green areas currently cover some 32 percent of Changsha's total
land area, or 10 percent more than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Hunan Province, one of the nation's major timber producers,
currently enjoys a forest coverage rate of some 51.1 percent, or
37 percent more than the national average. 
</P>
</TEXT>
