<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Economy Grows in First Half of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's gross domestic
product grew 4 percent in the first half of 1997, compared to a
drop of 1.5 percent in the same period of 1996, according to
latest data released by the Venezuelan central bank.
</P>
<P>
The economy shrank 1.6 percent in 1996, while inflation closed
at 103.2 percent, an unprecedented level for Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
Growth was seen in almost all the sectors of the economy during
the first half of 1997, particularly in those of construction,
with 14.3 percent, mining, 7.3 percent, communications, 5.8
percent, and commerce, 3.6 percent. 
</P>
