<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Restructuring Invigorates Public Bus Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The public bus sector in
Pudong is expected to erase losses and earn a profit this year
following the merger of the state-owned public bus company and
listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact the Pudong New Area is a national pacesetter
creating many economic miracles, public buses serving the areas
have long operated in a loss-making situation.
</P>
<P>
A bold plan to merge public bus companies with market-oriented
listed companies was introduced some 20 months ago to improve the
situation.
</P>
<P>
As a result, three shareholding public bus companies have been
formed on the basis of equity from the former Pudong Public
Transportation Company, five locally listed companies and a
company listed on the Hong Kong stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
The reform has thus far proved successful, with the new
companies gaining an increasing market orientation and flexible
operations.
</P>
<P>
For example, the recently incorporated Guanzhong company found
that the Lingzhao Residential Areas lacked public transport, and
within a mere 24 hours added a new route to the district. The new
route would have taken months and possibly even years to organize
under the old state planning system.
</P>
<P>
Some 37 public bus routes and 511 buses had been added to the
system by May of this year, raising available services in Pudong to
101 routes and 1,267 buses.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the administrative staff has cut dramatically to
improve efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The public bus sector is not expected to totally erase the 23
million yuan (2.77 million US dollars) in losses recorded last
year, but will nonetheless record some profits for this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
