<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Staffan De Mistura Appointed Director of UN Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today appointed Staffan De Mistura of Sweden as
director of the United Nations Information Center in Rome,
effective on September 1.
</P>
<P>
De Mistura served as the United Nations humanitarian
coordinator for Iraq from March through August 1997. Prior to
that, he held the posts of director of the Division of Public
Affairs of the United Nations Children's Fund and its
representative in Somalia.
</P>
<P>
De Mistura has served the United Nations in many other
capacities, including as director of fund-raising and external
relations of the United Nations Office of the Coordinator for
Afghanistan from 1988 to 1991, special envoy of the
secretary-general to Albania in 1990, director of the World Food
Program Operations in the Sudan in 1987 and as the Food and
Agricultural Organization's deputy chief de Cabinet from 1976 to
1985.
</P>
<P>
From 1987 to 1988, he was seconded director-general of the
World Wide Fund for Nature of Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
