<HEADLINE> Greece Condemns Jerusalem Bombings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece today condemned the
suicide bombings in downtown Jerusalem Thursday in which six
people were killed and over 160 wounded.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that nothing
could excuse "these abhorrent acts of violence."
</P>
<P>
"Such acts only confirm how necessary the peace process and
the recommencement of negotiations for their completion are," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Greek government expressed its deepest
condolences to the families of the victims and to the Israeli
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
