<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanon to Lodge Complaint Against Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon said it will lodge a
complaint against Israeli violation of truce with the five-nation
ceasefire committee regarding the heavy fighting in south Lebanon
early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese official National News Agency quoted Lebanese
Foreign Ministry officials as saying that the complaint will be
heard at a meeting of the committee expected to hold within 24
hours.
</P>
<P>
Twelve Israeli soldiers were killed, four others wounded, and
one missing when Lebanese army and resistance fighters ambushed a
16-member Israeli commando who landed on the village of Nsariyyeh,
about 45 kilometers north of the Israeli border in attempt to
explode a Shiite Movement Amal base near the village, the news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the battle, a Lebanese army position was hit and a
Lebanese woman and a baby girl were killed, six civilians wounded.
</P>
<P>
The officials considered the death of the girl who was then in
a car and the injuries of others as gross violations by Israel of
true understanding reached in April last year, saying that the
Lebanese delegation of the committee is waiting for a detailed
report on Israeli aggression to make a formal complaint.
</P>
<P>
The ceasefire committee, made up of delegates from the United
States, France, Israel, Syria and Lebanon, was established under
the true accord brokered by the U.S. to end a 16-day Israeli blitz
of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The committee is charged with overseeing the adherence to the
truce accord which prohibits attacks on civilians on both sides of
the border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
