<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Mourns Mother Teresa's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's ruling
African National Congress (ANC) expressed shock and sadness at
the death of mother Teresa, who passed away tonight after
suffering a heart attack.
</P>
<P>
In its statement, the ANC said mother Teresa's death was a
loss for all of humanity.
</P>
<P>
"We express our hope that her noble legacy will not be in vain
but will find fertile ground among nations of the world in their
endeavor to create a better life for all," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
"The ANC expresses its deepest condolences to members of the
community, the church, family, friends and colleagues during
these trying moments of their lives."
</P>
<P>
The opposition National Party joined the ANC in mourining
mother Teresa. "She will always be remembered as a symbol of love
and peace," the party spokesman Jan Bosman said.
</P>
<P>
"Her unselfish service to mankind, especially the poor and
destitute, is a monument of self-sacrifice," Bosman added.
</P>
</TEXT>
