<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Defense Secretary on Bosnia Peace Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary
George Robertson has raised the possibility that the NATO-led
peacekeeping mission in Bosnia might be extended beyond the
current mandate in June 1998.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a London meeting Thursday evening, Robertson said,
"I believe the international community should be reluctant to
leave a job half done after such a significant investment."
</P>
<P>
Though Robertson did not acknowledge that the mandate would
have to be extended, British government officials were quoted as
saying that Britain wanted other NATO members to address the
possibility that extension of the mandate would be necessary.
</P>
<P>
This crucial issue could be discussed at a meeting of NATO
defense ministers in the Dutch city of Maastricht in early
October, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
If the "follow-on" force in Bosnia were agreed, Robertson said,
"it will have to be NATO-led, with NATO-led credibility, and with
all the major players sharing the risks on the ground." 
</P>
</TEXT>
