<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Conference on Europe's Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VILNIUS, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The international conference
named Coexistence of Nations and Good Neighborly Relations -- the
Guarantee of Security and Stability in Europe opened today in
Lithuania's capital Vilnius.
</P>
<P>
The conference, initiated by Lithuanian President Algirdas
Brazauskas and his Polish counterpart, Alexander Kwasniewski,
was attended by the presidents of Belarus, Estonia, Latvia,
Ukraine, Bulgaria, Hungary, Finland, Moldavia and Romania and
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the international
conference, the Lithuanian president said, "By gathering in
Vilnius, we will have an opportunity to seek new ways of
implementation and practical application of the principles of
democracy, cooperation, security and good neighborly relations
enshrined in the Helsinki final act and other international
documents."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the states of Central and Eastern Europe, which
in this century suffered extremely painful blows of history, hold
a special role and responsibility in preventing a repeat of old
mistakes and, instead, by concerted joint efforts, overcoming the
current problems for the free, secure and prosperous Europe.
</P>
<P>
Brazauskas emphasized the task facing heads of state is to
create such an environment in the region which would bring people
closer to each other and become a reliable barrier against
incitement of animosity between them.
</P>
<P>
On European security, Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko said, "Europe seems to be missing a historic chance to
create a common family of nations and peoples enjoying equal
rights."
</P>
<P>
In his opinion, "the crucial mistake is a decision on the
expansion of NATO to the east," which, he said, poses a peril of
setting up new border lines if the cost of the expansion causes
the splitting-up of our continent, then this line of division will
on the border of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko noted, "We ought to do everything possible to
minimize the negative consequences of this erroneous step and not
to allow the coming back of animosity and suspicion in
relationship between our nations and peoples."
</P>
<P>
He also said that nothing unites people more than a common
activity and economic interests. Therefore, the European states
should pay special attention to the discussion of aspects of
regional and economic cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Also speaking at the opening ceremony, Russian Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin said Europe is going through a period of
profound transformations. He said, "A foundation for new relations
between the states is being laid and the shape of the future
European structure is being determined."
</P>
<P>
He said at present, European states have got a unique chance to
make the Baltic Sea, Central Europe and the Black Sea region one
of the generators of peace and cooperation in the entire Europe.
Russia sees the establishment of a new model of the Baltic-Black
Sea cooperation as an integral component of a new Europe, looking
forward to the 21st century, according to Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the conference agreed that after the cold war,
peace and development have become a main trend of the world, where
security and stability are the key of the trend. All the countries
of the world should make every effort to create a peaceful and
stable international environment, they stressed.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which was also attended by the representatives
of the European Commission and the Council of Europe, is expected
to end Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
