<HEADLINE> Britain's Queen Pays Tribute to Diana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Queen Elizabeth II
today paid tribute to Princess Diana as "an exceptional and gifted
human being."
</P>
<P>
In her live address to the nation this evening, the Queen said,
"Since last Sunday's dreadful news, we have seen throughout
Britain and around the world an expression of overwhelming sadness
at Diana's death. We have all been trying in our different ways to
cope."
</P>
<P>
This is the second televised address the Queen has made in
extraordinary circumstances since she came to the throne in 1952.
</P>
<P>
As a Queen, she said, "I want to pay tribute to Diana myself.
She was an exceptional and gifted human being. In good times and
bad, she never lost her capacity to smile and laugh, nor to
inspire others with her warmth and kindness."
</P>
<P>
On behalf of her family, the Queen expressed thanks to all who
have brought flowers, sent messages and paid respects in so many
ways to Diana.
</P>
<P>
She believed that there were lessons to be drawn from Diana's
life and the extraordinary and moving reaction to her death.
</P>
