<DOCNO> XIE19970906.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Nominates Congressman as Ambassador to Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton
today nominated Democrat congressman Thomas Foglietta to be U.S.
ambassador to Italy.
</P>
<P>
The White House announced Foglietta's nomination on the island
of Martha's Vineyard in Massachusetts, where Clinton was finishing
his vacation.
</P>
<P>
Foglietta, who speaks Italian and has deep family ties in
Italy, has represented the Philadelphia area in Congress since he
was first elected in 1980, according to an Associated Press
report.
</P>
<P>
The nomination needs to be confirmed by the Senate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
